@credibility text
Use credibility when several candidate variants exist for the same family and the runtime needs an explicit comparison rather than an accidental latest-value choice.
Prefer it for ranking, scoring, withdrawal decisions, or deciding whether more evidence is needed before downstream execution continues.
Its input should summarize candidates, provenance, criteria, and any evaluation hints that matter for fair comparison, so the outcome can be explained in traceability.
Avoid using credibility to generate brand-new answers; it is for comparing existing variants.
